My two year old son absolutely loves the newest cartoon series on nickelodeon, so when I caught the 3rd movie, Chipwrecked, on tv, I switched it over and he was hooked. Thank goodness I recorded it because he cried as it went off and I knew I had to find the others. I looked at a few other sites, but Amazon had it for such an amazing price! Especially for the first three! I had to buy them and I'm so glad I did. My son received them two days ago and has watched them non stop. I also love that with the first disc you have a choice of either full screen or widescreen. It's so nice for those of us who don't like wide screen. :)

This trio was seriously a lifesaver for us on a road trip . Nothing better than an occupied 7 year old than the headphones he wore while watching these . All we had to do was throw some food and drink at him on occasion and BAM ! Back to serenity.
But on a serious note , the deal is really an incredible value . You recieve all 3 feature movies . And they would cost a lot more if purchased separately.
We only have standard car and home DVDs players , but it's nice to have the blu Ray and digital copies that are included also .
If you want peace and quiet and peace of mind , these are great .

If you have the opportunity, I'd recommend Bluray. I purchased it on dvd and it was still good quality, however, if I made the purchase again, I would have chosen bluray. These are cute movies. This contains the first three movies. I know for sure they have four, but they may have more. The first one is the story about how they meet Dave and how the Chipmunks begin. The second one is when the girls enter the picture. The third one is where they all get stranded on an island. I would say I loved the first one, and I thought the second one was just as good. I think the third one was cute, but maybe not as good. It was still worth purchasing and watching. For someone who grew up in the 80s, these were good! And, if you are looking for your kids/grand kids, they are worth owning/watching. You will want to check the ratings, as I am uncertain if they are PG or G (not without looking). They are cute movies and they were written/produced/directed very well. I HIGHLY recommend.
